fields.title: Spider-Man: No Way Home
fields.review: With Spider-Man's identity now revealed, Peter asks Doctor Strange for help. When a spell goes wrong, dangerous foes from other worlds start to appear, forcing Peter to discover what it truly means to be Spider-Man.

fields.title: Prisoners
fields.review: When Keller Dover's daughter and her friend go missing, he takes matters into his own hands as the police pursue multiple leads and the pressure mounts.

fields.title: The Day After Tomorrow
fields.review: Jack Hall, paleoclimatologist, must make a daring trek from Washington, D.C. to New York City to reach his son, trapped in the cross-hairs of a sudden international storm which plunges the planet into a new Ice Age.

fields.title: The Power of The Dog
fields.review: Charismatic rancher Phil Burbank inspires fear and awe in those around him. When his brother brings home a new wife and her son, Phil torments them until he finds himself exposed to the possibility of love.

fields.title: Coda
fields.review: CODA's story offers few surprises, but strong representation and a terrific cast bring this coming-of-age story vividly to life.

fields.title: Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation
fields.review: Ethan and his team take on their most impossible mission yet when they have to eradicate an international rogue organization as highly skilled as they are and committed to destroying the IMF.

fields.title: Call Me by Your Name
fields.review: In 1980s Italy, romance blossoms between a seventeen-year-old student and the older man hired as his father's research assistant.

fields.title: Aquaman
fields.review: Arthur Curry, the human-born heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, goes on a quest to prevent a war between the worlds of ocean and land

fields.title: The Man From Toronto
fields.review: Starring Kevin Hart and Woody Harrelson, this mistaken identity film follows a sales consultant who is believed to be the world's deadliest assassin.

fields.title: Firestarter
fields.review: The Peacock reimaging of Stephen King's novel follows a parents on the run with their daughter Charlie from the government because she has the ability to create and control fire.
